section
  h3(id='res.location') res.location
  p.
    Set the location header.

  +js.
    res.location('/foo/bar');
    res.location('foo/bar');
    res.location('http://example.com');
    res.location('../login');
    res.location('back');

  p.
    You can use the same kind of <code>urls</code> as in
    <code>res.redirect()</code>.
    
  p.
    For example, if your application is mounted at <code>/blog</code>,
    the following would set the <code>location</code> header to
    <code>/blog/admin</code>:
    
  +js.
    res.location('admin')
